⦿ .spun — the five-fold spin of Relm Arrowny
node FF6 · FF6 · ⟦Relm Arrowny:FF6:39d277⟧

WHO   — Relm Arrowny — the child painter
WHAT  — A late-joining mage of Final Fantasy VI — the painter whose Sketch and Control turn image into action, who walks into a burning house to save a stranger and matches her elders barb for barb without ever lowering her brush.
WHERE — FF6 · Final Fantasy VI  Framework inputs: Final Fantasy VI (America's Final Fantasy III, 1994)  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — Because creation and life are the same act seen twice; because a child can hold more steel in her than the grown; because to paint a thing truly is to grant it a moment of being, and that is a power as holy as any spell.
HOW   — By the living magic of her brush — Sketch, that copies a foe's own attacks from a likeness, and Control, that bends a painted creature to her will — and by a fearless tongue that respects no one's dignity, least of all her own elders'.

awareness — what the node knows of itself:
  I am only a child with a brush — but what I paint is alive, and what is alive can fight, so do not mistake my size for my reach.

spoken token : dind-braeth-noth   ·   hex : 39d277
